Details

Job Posting Title:   SE_Project Manager_Senior
Description:

The Project Manager in Trade Navigation and Compliance is responsible for managing projects in purchasing focused on trade navigation and compliance, ensuring compliance with international trade regulations, standards, and best practices, interacting effectively with stakeholders, and identifying and resolving obstacles to completing the projects on time. It is vital to be aware of the regulations and legislations connected to Trade Navigation and to anticipate which ones impact the supply network.
See below for details on responsibilities, qualifications and skills.

----

Summary
Are you a project manager with extensive experience in trade navigation and compliance, as well as ISO
certification/compliance audits? Do you enjoy managing and delivering projects that involve cross-border
trade, regulatory compliance, risk management, and quality assurance? Do you have the skills to oversee
the purchasing process and coordinate with various stakeholders? Do you work proactively to anticipate
which regulations and legislations connected to Trade Navigtion impact the supply network?

Key Responsibilities
If you answered yes to these questions, you might be the perfect fit for our team. We are looking for a
project manager who can:
• Manage multiple, interrelated projects
• Manage and deliver trade navigation and compliance projects on time and scope, including
identifying and resolving problems that hinder project completion
• Organize project teams, assign individual responsibilities, develop project plans, and determine
resource requirements
• Identify and resolve obstacles to completing project scope on time
• Monitor and report on the status of projects and trade compliance activities
• Ensure compliance with international trade regulations, standards, and best practices
• Coordinate ISO certification/compliance audits
• Communicate and interact effectively with diverse stakeholders
• Work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced and diverse environment

Qualifications and Skills
To be successful in this role, you should have:
• In-depth experience in purchasing project management, trade navigation and compliance
• Strong knowledge of customs, export control, and other trade regulations
• Excellent communication, collaboration, and leadership skills
• Ability to work independently and handle complex problems
• Relevant work experience combined with a Bachelor's degree or higher in a related discipline
• Proficient in MS Office and SAP solutions

Senior: position typically requires >5 years relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

